# PEDAL (Cursor)

When the user works on features, planning, design/engineering docs, gap analysis, iteration, or completion reports, follow the **PEDAL** workflow defined in the repository.

## Canonical spec

Read and apply: **[.pedal/PEDAL.md](.pedal/PEDAL.md)**

It covers phases, directory layout, severity-weighted scoring, `.pedal-status.json`, templates under `.pedal/templates/`, and general rules (document language = user’s prompt language, git conventions).

## How to invoke (natural language)

Map user intent to phases (same as PEDAL.md):

- Plan / planning / requirements → **plan**
- Engineering / design / spec / architecture doc → **engineering**
- Implement / build / code → **do** (code only; no separate PEDAL doc)
- Gap analysis / verify vs spec → **analyze**
- Auto-fix / iterate / improve until thresholds → **iterate**
- Wiki + report / close cycle / PR → **learn**
- Archive finished docs → **archive**

## Cursor-specific

- Do **not** auto-switch to “Plan Mode” or similar isolated modes when writing the Plan; stay in normal agent mode and report progress (see PEDAL.md **plan** section).
- Prefer reading `.pedal/PEDAL.md` at the start of a multi-step PEDAL task so steps stay aligned with the single source of truth.

## Gemini CLI

Slash-command syntax for the same workflow lives in **[GEMINI.md](GEMINI.md)** (Gemini only).
